<Title>Warranty Alert
<Date>Thu Jan 18 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>This product comes with 90 day warranty and 1 year limited warranty. If you want a copy of the warranty, it's on the installation disc. My player quit functioning after about 4 months. The limited warranty is practically worthless. Creative charges your credit card if you want to talk with customer service after 90 days. E-mail support is free. They require the model #, which is not printed on the product or on the documentation. The model # is on their website, but Creative makes it difficult to obtain support. Creative sends form email instructing you to update the firmware. Before updating firmware you must back-up your music. The firmware update also removes the FM recording feature. It did not fix my player. If you return product for warranty service, Creative charges a fee for diagnosis and handling plus any added labor costs to fix the player. Bottom line, if your player breaks down after 90 days, it is probably not worth the time and money to obtain warranty service. I will not buy another product from Creative Labs. Try a quality brand.  
<Overall>1

