<Title>Zen Nano Plus:  A Very Decent MP3 Player
<Date>Fri Feb 23 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>For a purchase price of slightly less than $[...], the Zen Nano Plus offers some really nice features--assuming of course that 1 GB storage is ample for your needs.  The unit comes with a case and clip, suitable for either belt-attachment or to the included arm-band, headphones, adequate software, and an AAA battery.  The FM digital tuner is really awesome in its ability to accurately scan for local stations, lock them in with presets, allow for recording capability, and to provide incredibly clean, excellent sound from low to high frequencies.  Battery life varies, depending upon settings and use, and I don't regret investing in a couple of rechargeable NiMH 1.2 v 1000 mAh batteries instead.  The unit is well-built, the control buttons and scroller/select are well-placed, menu navigation easy, although the display numerics and icons might require reading glasses for some.  Other features & applications are very good, and this unit is significantly better than most MP3 players in its price range.  
<Overall>5

